The paper deals with the generation of synthetic fingerprints using machine learning techniques, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the legal restrictions on the use of biometric data, which is related to computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-category. The use of CycleGAN for image transformation is a multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the testing of the generated fingerprints using existing matchers involves information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
